snippet: Katie Rowan led the United States, scoring eight goals and adding two assists in a 19-5 victory over Canada in Oshawa, Ontario.
abstract: United States defeats Canada, 19-5, to take women's lacrosse World Cup title.
lead_paragraph: Katie Rowan led the United States, scoring eight goals and adding two assists in a 19-5 victory over Canada in Oshawa, Ontario.
